      <h1>FAQ</h1>

      <div id="questions" class="row">
        <div class="six columns">
		  <p>What's this ECS100/UI thing you keep talking about?</p>
		  <p>The ECS100 Jar is the ONLY external library permitted by BluJm rules. It is the library given to 100-level students at Victoria University of Wellington Engineering and Computer Science students and is the backbone of this competition.</p>

		  <p>Why can't I use X language instead of Java</p>
		  <p>Because for this event we want to focus on junior developers while giving a fun twist. Look out for Pxljm</p>

		  <p>Why can't I use X library/jar/engine (even though it's open source).</p>
		  <p>We have a hard rule on submissions not having any external dependencies of any kind. We discourage the use of code not written by your team members as it detracts from the original meaning of the game jam. You can however copy/combine/change your existing code to fit your project, meaning you could create an engine for your team before the competition (in fact, we encourage this). Look out for pxljm</p>

